    <h4>Description:</h4>
    <p>Egg Roll is a popular Indian street food made with a flaky paratha filled with a fried egg, vegetables, and tangy sauces.</p>

    <h4>Prep Time:</h4>
    <p>‚è±Ô∏è <strong>20 minutes</strong></p>

    <h4>Ingredients:</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>2 parathas or flatbreads</li>
        <li>2 eggs</li>
        <li>1 small onion (sliced)</li>
        <li>1 small cucumber (julienned)</li>
        <li>1 green chili (chopped)</li>
        <li>Chaat masala to taste</li>
        <li>Tomato ketchup & green chutney</li>
        <li>Salt to taste</li>
        <li>Oil or butter for frying</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Instructions:</h4>
    <ol>
        <li>Heat a tawa and cook the paratha until golden brown from both sides.</li>
        <li>Break one egg on the tawa, sprinkle some salt and place the paratha on top of it. Press gently so the egg sticks to the paratha.</li>
        <li>Flip and cook for a few seconds. Remove and keep warm.</li>
        <li>Spread ketchup and chutney, add onions, cucumber, green chili, and sprinkle chaat masala.</li>
        <li>Roll it tightly and wrap in foil or butter paper. Serve hot!</li>
    </ol>
